data.reddit:
Age: 30
Sex: female
Height: 5’10
Weight: 165 pounds 
Race: White European
Duration of complaint: 2-3 months
Location: UK, top of foot and thigh. 
Existing medical issues: migraine, anxiety. 
Current medication: 30mg amitriptyline daily to prevent migraine. 

Basically, I’m getting odd bodily feelings and I don’t know whether they are something I should see a doctor about, something normal that happens and isn’t a big deal, or something that’s a feature of anxiety. 

It started with a feeling in my upper thigh like a phone vibrating. I know phantom vibration is a thing (and the location is near where my phone usually is) so I figured it was that. However for about 2 or 3 months I’ve also been having this feeling in the top of my foot (same side as the feeling in my thigh). 

It’s sporadic and I think I can go days without it or sometimes have the feeling a couple of times a day persisting for a couple of minutes a time. It is not a usual feeling of pins and needles, more of a buzz. I’ve not been able to note any kind of pattern. It happens more often when I am sitting but has also happened when walking or driving. 

If relevant I had some lower back pain about 4 weeks ago which resolved itself in about 5 days with otc painkillers, and I have had on and off issues with anxiety throughout my life but they are particularly heightened at the moment and I am lined up for counselling starting in a few weeks.
